<TITLE>PRESIDENTIAL LIBRARY</TITLE>

<H2><I><CENTER><FONT SIZE ="+3">T</FONT>he <FONT SIZE ="+3">R</FONT>onald
 <FONT SIZE ="+3">R</FONT>eagan <FONT SIZE ="+3">P</FONT>residential
  <FONT SIZE ="+3">L</FONT>ibrary
 </CENTER></I></H2>
<HR WIDTH=50%>
<FONT SIZE= "+2">T</FONT>he Ronald Reagan Presidential Library is the ninth Presidential
Library  operated by the National Archives and Records Administration. 
It is an archival collection of the permanently valuable historical materials
of the Reagan Administration. Holdings presently consist of approximately
50 million pages of documents (23,5000 feet), including records created or
received by the President and White House staff members, approximately 1.5
million still photographs, and over 75,000 gifts. Before documents can be made
available to the public, they must be reviewed by archivists according to
the provisions of the Presidential Records Act of 1978. Currently, the Library
has opened approximately 7 million pages to researchers and scholars. There is 
also available a <A HREF =
"/townhall/hall_of_fame/reagan/libr/list.html">preliminary list</A> of presidential
records and historical materials in the Ronald Reagan Library.

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/townhall/hall_of_fame/reagan/library_facade.gif" WIDTH=400
HEIGHT=322>
<HR WIDTH=50%>
<B><CENTER>Ronald Reagan Presidential Library Floor Plan</CENTER></B>


<IMG SRC="/townhall/hall_of_fame/reagan/library_floorplan.gif" WIDTH=554
HEIGHT=201>
</CENTER>



<HR WIDTH=30%>
<CENTER>Ronald Reagan Presidential Library<BR>
40 Presidential Drive<BR>
Simi Valley, CA  93065<BR>
(805) 522-8444</CENTER>
</BODY>
